Looking at the proof goal, I need to prove that:
```
filter (flip all Chapter12.ok) (List.foldr (concatMap ∘ extendl) [[]] (a :: as)) =
    List.foldr (concatMap ∘ Chapter12.okextendl) [[]] (a :: as)
```

Let me simplify both sides using the definition of `List.foldr` on `a :: as`:

LHS: `filter (flip all ok) ((concatMap ∘ extendl) a (List.foldr (concatMap ∘ extendl) [[]] as))`
    = `filter (flip all ok) (concatMap (extendl a) (List.foldr (concatMap ∘ extendl) [[]] as))`

RHS: `(concatMap ∘ okextendl) a (List.foldr (concatMap ∘ okextendl) [[]] as)`
    = `concatMap (okextendl a) (List.foldr (concatMap ∘ okextendl) [[]] as)`

Using `h1` on LHS: `concatMap (okextendl a) (filter (flip all ok) (List.foldr (concatMap ∘ extendl) [[]] as))`

Using `ih`: `concatMap (okextendl a) (List.foldr (concatMap ∘ okextendl) [[]] as)`

Which equals RHS.

